Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) officers of the Mowe unit command in Ogun helped a pregnant mother on transit to a safe childbirth. Bisi Kazeem, Corps Public Education Officer, made this known in a statement on Saturday. The team, led by Deputy Route Commander (DRC) Damilola Osiyemi, assisted the woman who was in labour around 1430hours on Friday. The citizen, Mrs Ola of No. 7, Aiyegbami street in Sagamu, had boarded a vehicle with reg no FKJ 904 HE from Sagamu. “She was rushed to Broad Life Hospital, Olowotedo near NASFAT, Mowe, by the team. She was later delivered of a baby girl”, Kazeem said. The FRSC promised to continue to safeguard the lives and property of motorists and commuters across Nigeria. The statement reminded drivers to desist from overspeeding and violation of traffic rules.